In this example, **Distance Fields** collision is used for particle collision. The particles are always blocked by any surface that has a generated Distnace Field whether it's visible within the camera view or not. As
the camera moves under the tree, collision of particles on the surface of the tree top (out of the camera view) still affects the particles. 

