When **Scene Depth** collision is used for particle collision, the particles are only blocked by what is visible on with the camera view using the Scene Depth buffer. So, as the camera moves under the tree, collision
of particles on the surface of the tree top (out of camera view) is no longer affecting the particles causing them to fall on the ground in front of the camera even though they should be blocked.

